<HEADLINE> Extremist Crime in Rise in Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Right-wing extremist crimes in
Germany totaled 5,173 cases in the first nine months of this year,
up 14 percent from the same period of 1996, the mass-circulation
paper Bild reported today.
</P>
<P>
The number of right-wing radicals rose for the first time in
four years, up 2,000 to reach 47,000, showed statistics released
by German federal police authorities.
</P>
<P>
The official data also showed a surge in the popularity of
music with racist content during the period. The right-wing
extremist groups held a total of 79 concerts with up to 1,600
spectators for each.
</P>
<P>
The figure was more than double the number of such concerts
held in the year 1995, said the Bild report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
