<HEADLINE> Compaq Canada Ahead in PC Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Compaq Canada Inc. widened its
lead over IBM Canada Ltd. in the third quarter, getting almost
one-fifth of the country's personal computer market.
</P>
<P>
Compaq grabbed 18.9 percent of the consumer and corporate
market for PCs, up from 14.7 percent in the second quarter, said a
report today.
</P>
<P>
Second to Compaq was IBM, which had a 16.3 percent share of the
market. It was followed by Dell Canada, which had 6.9 percent of
the market, according to the Financial Post newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Much of Compaq's lead comes from spectacular growth in sales of
consumer products, especially its Presario line of PCs, analysts
said.
</P>
<P>
Ralph Hyatt, manager of product marketing at Compaq Canada,
said he expects the PC market to grow by up to 15 percent in the
country this year, with Compaq's share growing by four or five
times that rate.
</P>
<P>
He expects the smallest players in the PC industry will
continue to be squeezed out by competition on price.
</P>
<P>
The price cuts will continue, with reductions up to 10 percent
in 1998, he predicted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
