the expression in a report at today`s regular cabinet meeting,
Radio Jordan reported.
</P>
<P>
Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tariq Aziz is now in the United
Nations to seek ways to terminate the standoff with the United
States incurred by Iraq's decision on October 29 to expel all
the U.S. inspectors in the U.N. weapons inspection teams in
Baghdad.
</P>
<P>
Jordan urged to end the sufferings of the Iraqi people caused
by the U.N. sanctions imposed after Iraq's invasion of Kuwait in
1990, Mutawe said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the kingdom also urged Baghdad to comply with all
the U.N. Security Council resolutions concerning it, the
minister added.
</P>
<P>
Since Iraq announced the ban last month, Jordan has been
adopting a balanced attitude toward the issue, as both King
Hussein and Crown Prince Hassan said that the crisis should be
ended in a way that would guarantee the sovereignty and
territorial integrity of Iraq as well as pave the way for
implementation of U.N. Security Council's resolutions and the
lifting of the U.N. sanctions.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has barred U.N. weapons inspections teams that included
Americans for an eighth day. It has charged that the
U.S. inspectors are spies trying to prolong the U.N. sanctions.
</P>
