<HEADLINE> UNICEF Condemns Taliban's Detention of Its Staff Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Carol Bellamy,
executive director of the United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF),
today condemned the detention of two UNICEF staff members by the
Taliban, a warring faction of Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The two UNICEF staff members were detained by the Taliban in
Jalalabad on November 8. No concrete reason was offered for the
detention. The staff were taken to a public place where one man
was given 10 lashes in front of a crowd of onlookers. His
colleague managed to escape.
</P>
<P>
"The treatment of UNICEF staff is unacceptable affront to the
most fundamental principles of humanitarianism," said Bellamy in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
"UNICEF cannot and will not accept the intimidation and abuse
of staff who are working to provide for the needs of children
within a humanitarian framework. Such actions by the authorities
contravene long-established international protocols and
conventions for the protection of United Nations personnel
throughout the world," said Bellamy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
