<HEADLINE> UNHCR Donates 500 tents to Flood Affected People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, November 11 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) said it has donated some 500
tents for use by the flood affected persons in Dollo Area in
Ethiopia's Somali Region.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued here today by the UNHCR said these
tents were immediately distributed among individuals residing in
Dollo-Odo, Dollo-Bay and Suftu, who lost their houses as a result
of the flood.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR has been providing supplementary feeding to some 1,650
vulnerable refugees, including children, pregnant and lactating
women and the needy sick and elderly in three feeding sites at
Dollo-Odo, Suftu and Dollo-Bay since June this year, the release
said.
</P>
<P>
According to the release, the UNHCR has also donated essential
drugs to the local clinic for use by the refugees and the local
population.
</P>
<P>
The local population in and around Dollo in southern Ethiopia
have been seriously affected by erratic rains that caused the
overflowing of surrounding rivers, thus damaging their houses,
livestock and other property, the release explained.
</P>
<P>
There are an estimated 8,000 refugees of Somali origin
residing in Dollo Area, southern Ethiopia, receiving UNHCR
protection, the release added. 
</P>
