<HEADLINE> Cyprus, Algeria Sign Shipping Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus and Algeria signed
here today an agreement on shipping cooperation between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by Vassos Pyrgos, Cypriot Permanent
Secretary of Ministry of Communications and Works, and Chelghoum
Abdesselam, Secretary-General of Algerian Ministry of
Communications.
</P>
<P>
The agreement provides for equal treatment of each country's
vessels while docked in the other's ports, and the possibility
of employment for each country's seamen in ships under the flag
of the other.
</P>
<P>
It also provides for reciprocal recognition of the two
countries' ship-certificates and seamen's certificates, and for
the control of delays of ships.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Cypriot and Algerian ships are not
allowed to use closed ports to international navigation in the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
Pyrgos said the Cypriot government considers the agreement as
the beginning of a series of agreements and activities which will
promote co-operation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Abdesselam described the agreement as "a good
achievement" which marks a new era in bilateral relations.
</P>
</TEXT>
