<HEADLINE> Iraq Not to Change Decision on Banning US Inspectors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi Deputy Prime
Minister Tareq Aziz said here today that the Iraqi Government had
not changed its decision on banning Americans from U.N. weapons
inspection teams.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters, Aziz said, "I have not been given any
concrete promise that there will be a change in the position of
the Security Council of the United Nations."
</P>
<P>
