If you do not have a change on the part of the Security Council,
you cannot expect a change on the part of Iraq," he added.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of the American percentage of presence in the
inspection teams, Aziz said the Americans working in sensitive
United Nations Special Commission (UNSCOM) posts in the three
centers accounted for 44 percent last year and 32 percent this
year.
</P>
<P>
He said that Chileans manned and serviced UNSCOM's three
helicopters in Iraq and did not participate in the arms
inspection.
</P>
<P>
Aziz was responding to the remarks by Butler, the Chairman of
UNSCOM, who told reporters that Chileans were the largest group in
the arms inspection teams, accounting for 22 percent while
Americans accounted for 14 percent.  
</P>
