<HEADLINE> Women Seek Ways of Defending Their Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Cameroun's Minister of Women
and Social Affairs Yaou Aissatou has invited African women to
acquire the knowledge to be able to identify the violation of the
rights of the woman in their various areas.
</P>
<P>
According to Cameroun Tribune today, the minister made the
call here on Monday while opening an international seminar on the
protection and respect of woman's rights in Francophone Africa.
</P>
<P>
The minister underscored the reasons for the malpractices of
woman's rights tracing them to the customary laws, the
non-respect of existing laws, unprofessional conduct of legal
officials, discrimination and the relatively low literacy level
of women.
</P>
<P>
The women at the seminar are expected to arrive at solutions
to such nagging issues at the end of the seminar.
</P>
<P>
About 100 participants coming from 19 French speaking African
countries are taking part in the seminar.
</P>
<P>
The five-day seminar is jointly organized by the Canadian
Foundation for the Rights of People, the Canadian Cultural and
Technical Agency and the Canadian government as well as the
Camerounian government. 
