<HEADLINE> China, U.S., Sweden Divers Split Golds on Opening Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, November 12 (Xinhua) -- China, the United States
and Sweden split the three gold medals at stake on the opening day
of the 11th FINA World Junior Diving Championship here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's Anna Lindberg collected 430.62 points in the girl's
one-meter springboard in the 16-18 years age group to capture the
first gold in the championships.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Kotzian Ditte was second with 425.85 points, and
China's Yan Jie took the bronze.
</P>
<P>
Hu Jia of China was awarded 426.78 points to prevail in the age
14-15 three-meter springboard.
</P>
<P>
Kyung Min-kwon of South Korea finished second with 36.78 points
hehind Hu. China's Ho Wei placed third.
</P>
<P>
In the girls' age 14-15 platform event, American Erica Sorgi
won with 276.81 points. Australia's Anna McIlwaine and Kriystle
Delaforce took the next two places.
</P>
<P>
About 160 divers from 32 countries and regions are taking part
in the five-day meet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
