<HEADLINE> British Unemployment Falls 17-Year Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Unemployment fell by 9,500 to
1,464,300 in October, the lowest total for 17 years, showed
official figures today.
</P>
<P>
It was the 20th monthly drop in a row, but the smallest since
April 1996, according to the Office for National Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The number of working days lost through industrial disputes in
September was just 1,000.
</P>
<P>
The total of unemployment was the second lowest monthly figure
since records began in 1920. 
</P>
