<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Legislative Election Regulation Takes Effect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 12 (Xinhua) -- A regulation related to the
forthcoming legislative elections in the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region, proposed by the Electoral Affairs
Commission (EAC) and tabled at the Provisional Legislative
Council, came into effect today.
</P>
<P>
The document, entitled The EAC "(Registration) (Electors for
Functional Constituencies) (Voters for Subsectors) (Members of
Election Committee) (Legislative Council) Regulation," governs the
registration of electors for functional constituencies, voters for
the Election Committee subsectors and members of the Election
Committee.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the EAC said today: "We hope to enable the
registration work for functional constituencies and Election
Committee subsectors to start as soon as possible, given that the
registration for electors in geographical constituencies has
already started last Wednesday (November 5)."
</P>
<P>
The publication of the regulation in an extraordinary gazette
Monday would give as much time as possible to eligible persons and
bodies to be registered as electors-voters for functional
constituencies and the Election Committee before the registration
deadline set for January 16, 1998, according to the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
Explaining the main features of the regulation, he said that
the regulation provides a simplified procedure for registration by
way of a notification procedure.
</P>
<P>
To ensure the registration system works and to guard against
misuse of the information obtained by the Electoral and
Registration Officer for non-election purposes, the regulation
sets out various offenses, the spokesman said. The offenses
include:
</P>
<P>
-- making a false statement in relation to voter registration;
</P>
<P>
-- conspiring with, inciting, compelling, inducing, coercing,
intimidating or persuading another person to make such a false
statement;
</P>
<P>
-- obtaining information from a register or extracts of a
register and using it for a purpose other than in relation to the
election or imparting it to another person; and
</P>
<P>
-- failing to furnish information in response to a requirement
within the specified period.
</P>
<P>
The EAC, chaired by Justice Woo Kwok-hing, was established in
late September.
</P>
<P>
Under another legislative election-related regulation, which
was tabled at the Provisional Legislative Council last Wednesday,
30 of the 60 seats in the future legislature will be returned by
30 business and professional groups known as "functional
constituencies."
</P>
<P>
One-third of the seats will be returned by geographical
constituencies through proportional representation, and the
remaining 10 elected by an 800-member Election Committee.
</P>
<P>
In an earlier speech, Chief Executive of the SAR Tung Chee Hwa
said that the first legislative elections scheduled for next May
would be right on schedule and he pledged that they would be open,
fair and acceptable to people in the SAR.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
