<HEADLINE> Karachi Killing "Terrible and Tragic": UTP President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 12 (Xinhua) -- President of Union Texas
Pakistan (UTP) A. G. Hoffman today termed the killing of five of
its employees including four U.S. citizens as "terrible and
tragic."
</P>
<P>
Hoffman said in a statement issued in Karachi that the company
does not know the reason behind this attack and UTP is fully
cooperating with local officials in their investigations.
</P>
<P>
UTP, a subsidiary of Union Texas Petroleum Holdings Inc. based
in Pakistan's southern port city of Karachi, has about 500
employees. Some 300 are field workers and engineers and a dozen
are foreigners.
</P>
<P>
The company has so far invested about 300 million U.S. dollars
and has 45 oil and gas fields in Pakistan with most of them in
Sindh province. It produces 27,000 barrels of oil per day, about
50 percent of Pakistan's total oil output.
</P>
<P>
The four U.S. citizens and the Pakistani driver were gunned
down by some unidentified assailants at around 8:20 this morning
on their way from Karachi Sheraton Hotel to their office about
three kilometers away.
</P>
<P>
According to eye witnesses, the attackers were in a red Honda
Civic, which was later found abandoned in a nearby area.  
</P>
