<HEADLINE> Iranian FM Continues Gulf Tour In Qatar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Foreign Minister
Kamal Kharrazi arrived the Qatari capital Doha this morning on a
brief visit as part of his tour in the Gulf region to loosen
Tehran's long-term strained relations with its Arab neighbors.
</P>
<P>
It was the first travel for the Iranian minister since he took
his post in August.
</P>
<P>
The Qatari news agency said that upon his arrival, Kharrazi
hold talks with senior Qatari officials on bilateral relations
and discussed issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Non-Arab Iran has been trying to reach out to its Arab
neighbors across the Gulf since Iran's President Mohammad Khatami
formed a new government in August.
</P>
<P>
It is also making efforts to remove decades-old hostilities
against Tehran held by the Arab world, in particular by the Gulf
Arab countries. Iranian officials have described improved ties
with the Arab world as among Tehran's top priorities.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian foreign minister's tour came one month before the
Iran-hosted December 9 to 11 meeting of the Organization of the
Islamic Conference (OIC).
</P>
<P>
Iran feverishly hopes to make the meeting an unprecedented
gathering of foreign dignitaries. Around 50 heads of states,
including the Gulf Arab countries have been invited to the
convention.
</P>
<P>
Qatar is the fifth leg of Kharrazi's tour which has taken him
to Syria, Saudi Arabia, Oman and Bahrain. He will leave Doha
tonight for Oman and UAE to continue his tour. 
</P>
