<HEADLINE> S. Africa Firm on Diplomatic Ties With China: Nzo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, November 12 (Xinhua) -- South Africa is firm on
the establishment of diplomatic relations with the People's
Republic of China and wishes to foster closer cooperative ties,
Foreign Minister Alfred Nzo said in Cape Town today.
</P>
<P>
South African President Nelson Mandela announced on November
27, 1996 that his country would sever ties with Taiwan and
recognize the People's Republic of China by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Nzo said future cooperation between South Africa and China
should cover not only political and diplomatic spheres, but also
economic, trade, investment and other fields, officials with a
visiting Chinese delegation told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
In the meeting with a Chinese trade and economic mission, Nzo
said China had firmly supported the Southern African peoples in
their struggle for national independence and liberation and in
their fight against apartheid.
</P>
<P>
At present, China maintains close relations with the majority
of Southern African countries, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Nzo said South Africa also hopes that friendship and
cooperation between China and the Southern African Development
Community would be further enhanced, in addition to the good ties
between Beijing and Pretoria.
</P>
<P>
Head of the Chinese delegation, Shi Guangsheng, appreciated
the stance of the South African government on its diplomatic
recognition of China.
</P>
<P>
Shi is the deputy chief of China's Ministry of Foreign Trade
and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said the visit of such a large Chinese delegation on the
eve of the establishment of diplomatic ties between the two
countries demonstrated the constructive attitude of the Chinese
government toward the development of friendship and cooperation
with South Africa.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, he said, businessmen of the two countries
held fruitful discussions, which showed a great potential and
bright prospects in economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Shi hoped that the potential would be given a full play and
economic and trade cooperation could develop more quickly after
the establishment of diplomatic relations.
</P>
<P>
He said the development of cooperation between the two sides
are not only conducive to the economic development of the two
countries, thus benefiting the two peoples, but also to the
enhancement of cooperation between China and Africa, especially
Southern Africa.
</P>
<P>
Shi also conveyed to Nzo the greetings from Chinese vice
premier and foreign minister, Qian Qichen.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation, made up of major trade and economic
officials and representatives of about 55 leading Chinese
enterprises, arrived in Johannesburg on November 5 for an 11-day
tour.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, 18 contracts and protocols totaling 540 million
U.S. Dollars were signed between companies of the two countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
