<HEADLINE> Hydro-Electric Power Effort Underway in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Three government organs signed
an agreement here recently on the development of hydropower
resources of the Zagunao River in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
According to a plan of the Power Industry Ministry, the Sichuan
Provincial Planning Commission, and the government of Aba's
Tibetan-Qiang Autonomous Prefecture in Sichuan province, during
the first phase, five hydro-electric power stations will be built
on the river, with a combined capacity of 360,000 kw.
</P>
<P>
The Zagunao River in the Tibetan-Qiang Autonomous Prefecture is
168 kilometers long and has a drainage area of 4,632 sq.km. With a
drop of 3,092 meters, the river can be installed with generating
units with a combined capacity of 600,000 kw. It will be able to
generate three billion kwh of electricity a year when the first
phase project is completed.
</P>
<P>
Local officials say that the move will promote the development
of local mineral resources, tourism, and service trade
industries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
