<HEADLINE> Scientists Find Liver Cancer Patients Have Gene Defect </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Scientists at the Shanghai
Tumor Research Institute have discovered a gene defect in the
No.17 chromosome of liver cancer patients, a major step forward in
the basic research on liver cancer.
</P>
<P>
The scientists claimed that their discovery is the first of the
kind in the world. They also said they found the same problem in
patients from other places in addition to those in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
They believe this indicates that there may be some unknown
cancer gene connected with liver cancer or cancer-fighting gene
groups in the No.17 chromosome.
</P>
<P>
The State Science and Technology Commission has listed the
research project as one the major state medical science projects
and signed an agreement with the Genecore Bio-Technologies Inc. of
the United States to jointly continue the research. 
</P>
</TEXT>
