<HEADLINE> Chatchai Beats Arbachakov to Win WBC Flyweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's Chatchai Dutchboygym
stopped Russian Yuri Arbachakov with a unanimous decision to win
the World Boxing Council (WBC) flyweight title in Sapporo, Japan
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
American judges Dick Young scored it 117-111, Japan's Tamotsu
Tomihara counted it 116-113 and Jose Juan Guerra of Mexico had it
119-111, all in favour of the Thai boxer.
</P>
<P>
It was sweet revenge for Chatchai, who dropped to Arbachakov by
a unanimous decision in their previous fight in September 1995.
</P>
<P>
Chatchai, 27, extended his record to 31 wins, including 24
knockouts, against one defeat.
</P>
<P>
For Arbachakov, it was his first-ever defeat after winning his
previous 23 bouts in a row, including 16 knockouts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
