<HEADLINE> Taiwan Democratic Self-Government League Celebrates 50th Anniversary (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth National Congress of
the Taiwan Democratic Self-Government League, one of China's eight
leading non-communist parties, opened today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, also marking the 50th anniversary of the
organization, will study the guidelines of the 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC), examine a report
delivered by the Fifth Central Committee of the league, approve the
league's constitution and elect the Sixth Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Chinese leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi and Li Ruihuan,
wrote inscriptions for the 50th anniversary of the Taiwan
Democratic Self-Government League.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, general secretary of the CPC Central Committee and
Chinese president, wrote: "Carry forward the tradition of loving
the motherland and the hometown, and promote the peaceful
reunification of China."
</P>
<P>
The inscription by Premier Li Peng was to "extensively unite
the Taiwan compatriots, and strive for the reunification of the
motherland."
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi, chairman of the National People's Congress (NPC),
wrote: "Promote the cross-strait exchanges, and continue to work
hard for the reunification of the motherland."
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), wrote: "Unite
the Chinese people and push for the reunification of the
motherland."
</P>
<P>
Cai Zimin, executive president of the meeting, delivered an
opening speech. After summarizing the four pieces of the
experience obtained by his league in the past 50 years, he said
the call made by the 15th CPC National Congress on the peaceful
reunification would be important and positive to develop the
relations between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
The concept of "peaceful reunification and one country, two
systems" came true in Hong Kong, he said, adding that "we should
give full play to the advantages of the Taiwan Democratic
Self-Government League, develop various cross-strait exchanges
including personnel contacts, and boost political talks between
the two sides."
</P>
</TEXT>
