<HEADLINE> NPC Vice-Chairman Meets with U.S. Senator </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Wang Bingqian, vice-chairman
of the Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's
Congress (NPC), met here today with U.S. Senator Frank Murkowski,
chairman of the Energy and Natural Resources Committee.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting in the Great Hall of the People, Wang said
one of the important common points that Chinese President Jiang
Zemin and U.S. President Bill Clinton agreed upon during Jiang's
recent U.S. visit was to strengthen Sino-U.S. cooperation in the
fields of energy and environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
Such cooperation is an important point in a joint statement
issued by the leaders of the two countries, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that legislature-to-legislature cooperation
constitutes a major part of bilateral relations. He said the
Chinese government puts great importance on expanding the friendly
cooperative relations between the NPC and the U.S. Congress.
</P>
<P>
Wang said he hopes that the two sides will work together to
implement the agreements and common points that the heads of the
two nations have reached.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that Murkowski's visit will have a
positive impact on the promotion of friendly cooperative relations
between the two countries and their legislatures.
</P>
<P>
Murkowski said he will continue to push for cooperation between
the two countries and two legislatures in all fields. He pointed
out that the two nations should handle bilateral relations
properly by adopting an attitude of seeking common points without
being negatively affected by their differences.  
</P>
