<HEADLINE> US Caterpillar Distributor Opens in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The Lei Shing Hong Machinery
Co. Ltd. transportation center, the first distributor for US-based
Caterpillar, opened Monday in Kunshan of east China's Jiangsu
Province.
</P>
<P>
The Lei Shing Hong Group, a listed transnational company
headquartered in Hong Kong, is mainly involved in the automobile,
real estate, foreign trade, investment and heavy equipment
sectors.
</P>
<P>
Lei Shing Hong Machinery is the first authorized distributor of
Caterpillar heavy equipment in Jiangsu, Zhejiang, Anhui and Hubei
provinces, as well as in the Three Gorges Area and Shanghai,
according to Liu Chuqun, chairman of the Lei Shing Hong Group.
</P>
<P>
The transportation center, established with a total investment
of 13.5 million U.S. dollars, covers 55,000 square meters.
</P>
<P>
Caterpillar, which is headquartered in Peoria, Illinois, in the
world's largest manufacturer of heavy equipment. The company's
heavy equipment, including bulldozers, end loaders and
dump-trucks. have been used extensively at China's massive Three
Gorges Project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
