<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Beats Kuwait 1-0 in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, November 12 (Xinhua) -- China beat Kuwait 1-0 in their
last soccer World Cup Asian Zone qualifying match here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Chinese midfielder Ma Mingyu scored the winning goal in the
32nd minute, when he delivered a surprise 20-yard blast from
center to beat Kuwait's goalkeeper Al J. Ahmad.
</P>
<P>
China dominated most of the group A match, which saw the two
sides play for pride as both had no chance to make the World Cup
finals in France next summer.
</P>
<P>
Referee Angeles Arturo of the United States flashed five yellow
cards, booking China's Fan Zhiyi and Sun Jihai.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait's Al S. Nohayr, Al S. Hani and Al S. Naser were also
booked.
</P>
<P>
Chinese coach Qi Wusheng said: "Our players played
conscientiously and to their best. However, we still appeared
infrior to the Kuwait players as far as passing and tactical
awareness are concerned.
</P>
<P>
"We won the match just because of the long blast from the
midfielder Ma Mingyu." added Qi, who has guided the Chinese
national team for five years.
</P>
<P>
When asked whether he would resign after the failure to
qualify, he said, "I did not finish my work in a satisfactory
manner in this period of time. Whether to stay in the job or quit
is the question I would have to decide soon."
</P>
<P>
Kuwait's coach Milan Macla said: "In the first half we had good
opportunities and the goalkeeper helped us a lot. But from these
opportunities we did not score."
</P>
<P>
China finished fourth in the group with 11 points and Kuwait
bottom at 8.
</P>
<P>
Iran, who have had played all its group matches, collected 12
points, followed by Saudi Arabia at 11 and Qatar at 10 with one
game remaining.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia will meet Qatar in the remaining match later on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
If the two sides drew, Iran will qualify for France as the
group winner and Saudi Arabia be the runner-up. If either side
win, the victor will qualify for France and Iran will be placed
second.
</P>
<P>
The second-placer has to face group B runner-up Japan in a
play-off in a neutral venue on November 16.
</P>
<P>
The winner of that play-off qualified for France while the
loser meets Australia on home and away on November 22 and 29 for a
berth in the finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
