<DOCNO> XIE19971112.0116 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ramos to Raise Specific Proposals on Financial Mechanism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos said today that he will bring up specific proposals for a
financing mechanism to solve the currency woes besetting Southeast
Asia at the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) meetings in
Vancouver this month.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said he was getting "a very good response" from his
fellow leaders of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN) and Japan to his soundings for a cooperative approach to
the currency crisis.
</P>
<P>
He indicated that specifics on the proposed mechanism would be
worked out during the meeting of ASEAN vice financial ministers
and deputy governors of central banks to be held in Manila on
November 17 and 18.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said ASEAN trade ministers have also responded to the
calls for the establishment of the mechanism, adding that he is
also getting inputs from the private sector and top business
leaders in the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Ramos said that he will seek APEC's endorsement for
the financial mechanism that would augment the resources provided
by the International Monetary Fund (IMF) in the region.
</P>
<P>
"This would assure economies of the availability of financing
as they pursue needed reforms and adjustment measures in
conjunction with the IMF," he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he said he would also seek the APEC leaders'
cooperation in promoting sound practices to reinforce
macro-economic fundamentals, supervising the banking system,
developing the capital market and improving transparency in the
region.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
