<DOCNO> XIE19971112.0117 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Athletes Honored for Good Show at Masters Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 12 (Xinhua) -- "The long-standing efforts
by Hong Kong's two provisional Municipal Councils to promote
sports for people of all ages has paid off as we see the excellent
performance by the Hong Kong, China delegation at the Australian
Masters Games," the delegation's leader Chow Yick-hay said here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Chow, a Provisional Regional Councilor, was speaking at a party
here today celebrating the delegation's success at the October
24-November 1 Games in Canberra, Australia.
</P>
<P>
Chow said that the two Councils have been encouraging
mature-aged residents to exercise during their pastime and to
participate in other recreational activities for the benefit of
their mental and physical well-being.
</P>
<P>
Fred Li Wah-ming, a Provisional Urban Councilor and the
delegation's other leader, owed the success to the hard training
by athletes themselves, as well as high moral among delegation
members during the Games.
</P>
<P>
"And it has proved that the Councils' efforts in
promoting 'Sports for All' had not been wasted," he added.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, sent by the two provisional Municipal Councils
to the Games, netted a total of 26 gold, eight silver and 13
bronze medals in swimming, bowling, table tennis and badminton
events.
</P>
<P>
Of the medals, eight gold and a bronze medals were taken by
China's former national swimming team member Fu Tai-Hun. Fu, now
60, also set new Games records in five individual and two relay
events.
</P>
<P>
Tenpin bowling athlete Wong Chun-ngok, 41, won four medals and
was presented at the Games a special award for nearly achieving
full score in the men's singles by gaining 297 points.
</P>
<P>
The Canberra Games were specially organized for veteran
sportsmen and sportswomen aged over 35. Some 10,000 athletes from
Australia and about 20 other countries and regions participated in
this year's Games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
