<HEADLINE> Netherlands Opens Trade Office in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The Netherlands Council for
Trade Promotion has opened a representative office in Chengdu, the
capital of southwest China's Sichuan province.
</P>
<P>
Up to now the organization has offices in Nanjing, Wuhan,
Ji'nan, and Chengdu.
</P>
<P>
The Netherlands and Sichuan co-operate in agriculture, animal
husbandry, industry, and technology, according to its Ambassador
to China Ate Oostra, who spoke at the opening ceremony of the
office in Chengdu yesterday. The Netherlands has 23 enterprises in
finance, metallurgy and machinery in Sichuan, Oostra said.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan has 6,740 projects with direct foreign funding valued
at 8.16 billion U.S. dollars, making it first in China's central
and western regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
