<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Three Red Cards in One Match Earn Player Long Ban </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Aberdeen forward Dean Windass
was banned for six weeks on Wednesday after being booked three red
cards in the same game against Dundee United on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Referee Stuart Dougal initially sent off Windass for two
bookable offences. But his dissent at the referee earned the
equivalent of another red card.
</P>
<P>
On his way to the tunnel, the 28-year-old Englishman lost his
temper entirely, ripping the corner flag from the ground and threw
it down -- which earned him another red card.
</P>
<P>
He will be sidelined until December 27 as well as being fined
two weeks salary by his club. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
