<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taiwan Democratic Self-Government League Contributes to Reunification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The Taiwan Democratic
Self-Government League, composed mainly of Taiwan compatriots
residing on the Chinese mainland, has contributed a great deal to
the peaceful reunification of the motherland by implementing the
guidelines and policies of the Communist Party of China toward
Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Kehui, executive president of the Sixth National Congress
of the league, made the remarks at today's opening of the
congress in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
He said it is important for the league to strengthen exchanges
between compatriots on the two sides of the Taiwan Strait, to
fight against separation of Taiwan from the motherland and "Taiwan
independence" as well as foreign interference into China's
internal affairs, to maintain the basic interests and legitimate
rights of the Taiwan compatriots, and to promote the reunification
of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, the Taiwan Democratic Self-Government
League has gone all out to boost cross-strait relations, Zhang
said.
</P>
<P>
For instance, he said, his league studied the changes of the
situation of Taiwan in 1992, and made suggestions to related
departments.
</P>
<P>
After President Jiang Zemin made his eight-point propositions
on the Taiwan issue in 1995, his league and the All-China
Federation of Taiwan Compatriots held meetings urging the Taiwan
authorities to respond quickly, he added.
</P>
<P>
To push forward the cross-strait relations, Zhang said, his
league also invited and received Taiwan compatriots from Taiwan
Island and overseas, and assisted some related departments to
smooth difficulties of Taiwan's investors on the mainland.
</P>
<P>
In the past five years, the league has received some 10,000
Taiwan compatriots and assisted in introducing investments from
Taiwan worth 2.9 billion yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
