<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asian Advertising Congress Opens in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Some 1,600 advertising
executives from 16 countries gathered here today for a four-day
meeting to discuss issues and trends affecting the advertising
industry, particularly in Asia.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony of the 20th Asian Advertising
Congress (AdAsia), Philippine President Fidel Ramos called on
advertising executives to continue their efforts to draw the
attention of the world to the continuing growth in the Asian
region.
</P>
<P>
The congress will tackle issues such as the role of Asia in
global network plans in the industry, growing similarities of
conditions between the East and West and the search for the best
regional model with regards to advertising self-regulation.
</P>
<P>
A major part of the congress is a trade exhibit which will show
the newest products, equipment and technologies that influence the
way advertising is seen, heard and felt.
</P>
<P>
AdAsia is a biennial advertising congress of the Asian
Federation of Advertising Associations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
