<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-12 13:12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iraq Again Bars Americans Inspectors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, November 12 (Xinhua) -- For the ninth time in 10 days,
Iraq blocked Americans from entering a weapons inspection site
Wednesday in defiance of pressure for it to back down.
</P>
<P>
Five weapons inspection teams left the U.N. headquarters in
Baghdad at 9:30 a.m. today and headed for the sites they desired
to inspect in and near the capital.
</P>
<P>
As one of the teams arrived at a Baghdad site, the Iraqis in
charge refused to let it in because there were American members in
the mission. The inspectors turned back to their headquarters and
the other four teams then followed suit, according to the official
news agency.
</P>
<P>
Iraq decided on October 29 not to allow American members of the
U.N. arms inspection teams to participate in the U.N. mission,
accusing them of working for Washington, not for the U.N..
</P>
<P>
In a few hours today, the U.N. Security Council is to vote on a
U.S. and British resolution which would pressurize Iraq into
complying with the council resolutions and condemn its tampering
with weapons inspections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
