<HEADLINE> Deputy FMs of Iran, Croatia Meet on Bilateral Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister
for Euro-American Affairs Morteza Sarmadi has stressed the
importance of peaceful cooperation and coexistence among the
Balkan states, the official news Agency IRNA reported today.
</P>
<P>
Sarmadi held a meeting Tuesday with his Croatian counterpart Ivo
Senader, who was on a three-day visit to Iran.
</P>
<P>
Sarmadi said Iran has always paid special attention to the
Balkans and has played an active role in countering aggression and
defending the legitimate rights of the peoples in the region.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he said, Iran has never sought to impose its views
on the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
Senader voiced his country's willingness to boost all-out
cooperation with Tehran, saying that as the two countries are
located in very sensitive and important regions, their
consultations have assumed an even greater importance.
</P>
<P>
The Croatian official, who arrived here Tuesday morning,
briefed Sarmadi of the latest developments in the Balkans, saying
that Zagreb will strive to terminate the mission of the
international forces stationed in Croatia.
</P>
<P>
The same day, Senader also held a meeting with Iranian Deputy
Foreign Minister for Economic Affairs Mahmoud Vaezi, during which
he said that the third session of Iran-Croatia joint economic
commission will have a positive impact on expansion of
Tehran-Zagreb cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that the signing of agreements on elimination of
double taxation and promotion of joint investment could serve as
the basis for Tehran-Zagreb cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Vaezi welcomed Croatian proposal on holding meetings to
strengthen bilateral economic relations, calling for expanding
Tehran-Zagreb economic and industrial cooperation in the fields of
shipbuilding, purchasing and repairing locomotives and wagons,
using ports facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
