<DOCNO> XIE19971112.0127 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Burn Research Reaches Molecular Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Experts have claimed
that China's research on burns has reached the molecular level.
</P>
<P>
The conclusion was made at the 5th national conference of the
Chinese Society of Burn Surgery of the Chinese Medical
Association, which was recently held in Chongqing.
</P>
<P>
The level of China's study on burn injury has developed into a
micro world, from studying the changes of burned cells to that of
the cell molecules, according to Xiao Guangxia, president of the
Chinese Society of Burn Surgery.
</P>
<P>
Chinese medical circles have successfully combated enterogenous
infection and endogenous toxin, and in general deepened their
understanding of burns.
</P>
<P>
China's study on burn injuries, among the most advanced in the
world since the 1970s, has formed a set of Chinese-style
treatments, particularly for healing a wounded surface, and taking
preventive measures to keep burn patients from going into shock.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 200 experts along with 530 representatives attended the
conference. The 1,445 academic papers presented showed that China
has made new progress on the emergency treatment,
anti-complication and anti-infection procedures for burns. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
