<HEADLINE> Use of Foreign Funds for Fujian Hydropower Plant Approved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The State Planning Commission
has approved the feasibility study for the use of foreign funds
for building a 600,000-kw hydropower plant in east China's Fujian
Province.
</P>
<P>
The hydropower station, which will be built on the Tingjiang
River in Fengshi Township, Yongding County, will require total
investments of 5.16 billion yuan (621.69 million U.S. dollars),
including loans of 160 million U.S. dollars from the Asian
Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
The plan calls for the river to be dammed in September next
year, with the first unit of generators scheduled to go online in
July 2001. The hydropower plant will have an annual generating
capacity of 1.51 billion kw/hr.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary construction for the station is proceeding on
smoothly, with a 346-m water diversion tunnel scheduled for
completion by the end of this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
