<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed
lower against its United States counterpart today despite
receiving support from good exporter buying.
</P>
<P>
The local unit settled at 69.85 US cents, down from 69.94 in
Sydney previously but higher than the session's open of 69.78
cents.
</P>
<P>
John Radinoff, a foreign exchange executive, said the local
currency had "held up pretty well" because of exporter interest
despite falls on regional stock markets.
</P>
<P>
However, Radinoff said pressure remained to the downside for
the Australian dollar in the near term in the light of global
financial market concerns.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar finished also at 87.60 yen, from 87.31 in
Sydney previously, and at 1.1934 marks, from 1.1886.  
