<HEADLINE> Uganda Coffee Exports Decline in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Uganda exported 130,829 bags
of coffee (60 kilograms per bag) in October in comparistion with
220,072 bags in September, The New Vision reported today.
</P>
<P>
The FOB (free on board) value free of insurance and
transportation charges was 12.14 million U.S. dollars in
October, as against 18.54 million dollars in September, it added.
</P>
<P>
Citing the figure from Uganda Coffee Development, the report
said that coffee exports declined by 61.6 percent, over 340,000
bags in last October. The value of coffee export for October
last year was 26.81 million of U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The projected volume of coffee export for October this year
was 320,000 bags with the value of 26.8 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The decreasing of the volume and the value in October this
year were attributed to long dry season from July to September.
</P>
<P>
Coffee is the most important export in Uganda, which accounts
for 65 percent of the country's total export value. 
</P>
</TEXT>
