<HEADLINE> India Eyes Global Perfumery Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 12 (Xinhua) -- With its strong basis in
agriculture, India can successfully tap the 10 billion U.S. dollar
global perfumery intermediates market, a study shows.
</P>
<P>
A large number of extraction units have been set up in the
country in the small and medium sector for producing concrete and
essential oils which are intermediates used in the perfumery
industry, said the study conducted by the Industrial and Technical
Consultancy Organization of Tamil Nadu Ltd. (ITCOT), which is
available here today.
</P>
<P>
Perfumery intermediates are used in manufacturing soaps,
detergents, disinfectants, room sprays, paints and cosmetic
powders.
</P>
<P>
Based on the study, the ITCOT has presented a report entitled
"Opportunities in Perfumery Industries", listing the opportunities
and prospects for this industry in the global scenario.
</P>
<P>
The report proposed a number of non-synthetic, non-pollution
and eco-friendly projects to produce quality perfumery
intermediates.
</P>
<P>
The ITCOT also suggested that Indian entrepreneurs target
products like menthol, basil, jasmine, lemon grass and eucalyptus
for producing essential oils and concrete. 
</P>
</TEXT>
