<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Round up Street Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, November 12 (Xinhua) -- An operation to round
up street children in Mwanza Municipality in northwest Tanzania
will be launched in a bid to curb the rising crime rate.
</P>
<P>
Street children, walking the Mwanza streets, reportedly rob
women and snatch their necklaces, earrings and other personal
effects, said Justice Gosbert, the district administrative
officer.
</P>
<P>
Parents also complained that street children beat pupils with
knives or razor blades, the official said, quoted by a report in
The Guardian today.
</P>
<P>
School students have admitted that they were being harassed
by street children in the area. "They force us to smoke
marijuana. If we refuse they smear us with human feces,"
complained Yahya Abudu, a pupil at Nyamagana Primary School.
</P>
<P>
School girls have received worse treatment at the hands of
Nyamagana street boys. Some girls have been tortured, narrowly
escaping being raped by the street children who use the Nyamagana
as their hideout. 
</P>
</TEXT>
