<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S.-based Energy Giant Enron to Invest More in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The United States-based
world energy major Enron International Ltd. has drawn up a major
investment plan to tap the Indian Market, Enron sources said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The two-phased strategy includes a pipeline project from
Bangladesh to India and a gas plant on the eastern coast in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Enron, which is developing the Dabhol power project in the
southwest Indian state of Maharashtra, has now decided to focus on
India and Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Enron has proposed to carry out a cluster of power projects in
southern India that will produce around 5,000 megawatt (MW) of
electricity. It has already contracted a 2,000 MW power plant
project in Ennore of Tamil Nadu and a 500 MW project in Kerala
state.
</P>
<P>
Under its medium-term strategy, the Enron company is
negotiating with exploration companies in Bangladesh on building a
gas pipeline from Bangladesh to India to supply natural gas to
bulk consumers of steel, power and fertilizer companies on the
east coast.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
