<DOCNO> XIE19971112.0151 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Refereeing Decisions Cannot Be Overturned: FIFA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, November 12 (Xinhua) -- World soccer's ruling body FIFA
reiterated in Zurich on Wednesday that all refereeing decisions
were final and could not be overturned at a later date by an
outside body.
</P>
<P>
FIFA declared in a statement void a German federation move to
order a replay after TV footage showed the referee was wrong to
award a goal in a Bundesliga match.
</P>
<P>
It stressed that its Committee for Legal Matters had ruled that
all decisions, especially whether a goal has been scored or not,
could not be overturned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
