<DOCNO> XIE19971112.0152 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia, China to Further Economic Cooperation: Nemtsov </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Russia gives priority to
economic cooperation with China, Russian First Vice Premier Boris
Nemtsov said here Tuesday night.
</P>
<P>
Nemtsov, who accompanied Russian President Boris Yeltsin on his
visit to China on November 9-11, said the most important results
of the talks include a major agreement on development of the
Kovyktinsky gas deposit in the Irkutsk Region, Western Siberia.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the two sides also reached understandings on
possible cooperation in transporting Russian gas to China via
Western Siberia and on the construction by Russia of a nuclear
power plant in China, Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
"These agreements are absolute priorities for us," he said.
</P>
<P>
The vice premier also noted that much attention was given to
regional cooperation, including that in border areas between the
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
