<HEADLINE> Pakistan Court Issues Notices to PM in Contempt Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Supreme Court
today issued show cause notices in a contempt of court petition
against 12 respondents including Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif.
</P>
<P>
The respondents have been asked to appear on November 17 to
explain as to why contempt proceeding should not be initiated
against them.
</P>
<P>
A three-member bench of the Apex Court, headed by Chief Justice
Sajjad Ali Shah, did not accept the plea of Mohammad Zafar, the
counsel of Nawaz Sharif to allow one month's period to file reply
to the petition.
</P>
<P>
The petition was filed by Chaudhry Muhammad Akram, Additional
Secretary General of the Supreme Court Bar Association.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
