<HEADLINE> World Mayors to Meet in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, November 12 (Xinhua) -- More than 350 mayors from
worldwide will meet at the World Conference of Mayors between
November 16 and 19 in the Nigerian capital Abuja, the local press
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Jeremiah Useni, Minister of Federal Capital Territory
disclosed this Tuesday in Abuja at the inauguration of the
organizing committee, which is headed by Useni.
</P>
<P>
This would be the first time for Nigeria to host the World
Conference of Mayors since the latter came into existence in the
1980s, the press reports said.
</P>
<P>
During their stay in Abuja, the mayors will also be invited to
visit Lagos, Port Harcourt, Kano, Enugu and other parts of the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
