<HEADLINE> Trade Union Leader Meets Japanese Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing, a member of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), met today with a
Japanese delegation headed by Hashimoto Mutsumi, director of the
Intl, Contacts Dept. of the Kansai Productivity Center, and his
party.
</P>
<P>
Wei, who also serves as member of the Secretariat of the CPC
Central Committee and president of the All-China Federation of
Trade Unions (ACFTU), briefed the Japanese delegation on the 15th
National Congress of the CPC, China's resumption of sovereignty
over Hong Kong, and the nation's labor policies.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese delegation, visiting China as guest of the ACFTU,
will attend the Third China-Japan Symposium on Labor Issues
scheduled for sessions in Beijing and Guangzhou between November
13-15.
</P>
<P>
The Japanese Productivity Center, a semiofficial organization
composed of representatives from government departments, trade
unions and employers, is headquartered in Osaka.  
</P>
