<HEADLINE> Share Prices End Steady on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Share prices moved within a
narrow range on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits
Times Industrials Index closed marginally higher at 1685.79 points
today, up by merely 1.69 points from Tuesday's finish.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased a bit to 143.88 million
units, valued at 286.64 million Singapore dollars (about 182.57
million US dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 271 to 77,
while 264 other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
JIT was the most actively traded counter as it registered a
turnover of 36.51 million units. It was followed way behind by the
Singapore Telecom which had 6.004 million shares traded. The Hong
Kong Land was next with 4.34 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Uniphoenix led the gainers of the day as it rose by 60 cents to
finish at 6.1 Singapore dollars. NBT increased by 50 cents to end
at 23.6 Singapore dollars, while the Keppel Corporation gained 25
cents to close at 5.4 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 was the biggest loser as it
declined by 1.1 dollars to end at 44.1 Singapore dollars. The
Asean Fund fell by 80 cents to close at ten Singapore dollars. The
DBS (Development Bank of Singapore ) Foreign and Elec lost 50
cents each to finish at 14.6 Singapore dollars and 6.85 US dollars
respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
