<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israel Defense Minister to Visit Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Defense Minister
Yitzhak Mordechai will visit Ankara next month in a bid to
strengthen military ties with Turkey, Israel Radio reported today.
</P>
<P>
Mordechai's visit comes at the invitation of his Turkish
counterpart Ismet Sezgin. Heading a big military delegation,
Mordechai will focus on military cooperation during talks with
Turkish President Suleyman Demirel, Prime Minister Mesut Yilmaz
and other Turkish leaders.
</P>
<P>
Details of fixing a date for the controversial
Turkish-Israeli-U.S. joint naval maneuvers will be worked out
during Mordechai's visit, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
The maneuvers have been planned for next January and are to be
held off the Israeli coast.
</P>
<P>
Mordechai's discussions in Turkey are also expected to cover
numerous defense issues and joint projects. The two countries have
considered plans to set up a satellite communication system to
create a safe intelligence link between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Israel has reportedly begun delivery of air-to-ground,
stand-off precision-guided Popeye missiles to Turkey. At least 40
Popeye missiles, with a range of 150 kilometers, will be
delivered to Turkey this year. Ankara is expected to buy 60 more
such missiles from Israel next year.
</P>
<P>
Israel and Turkey are planning to cooperate on a joint project
to produce Delilah and Arrow long-range missiles, which can reach
targets in 500 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have been exchanging intelligence information.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Mordechai also is expected to try to
convince Turkey to open the way for modernizing Turkey's aging
M-60 tanks. Israel is bidding to refit Turkey's 48 F-5 war planes
and to replace Turkey's G-3 infantry weapons with Israel-made
Galil assault rifles.
</P>
<P>
Israel Aircraft Industries is upgrading 54 Turkish F-4s in a
632-million-U.S.-dollar deal.
</P>
<P>
Israeli-Turkish military cooperation has been generating
fears in the Arab world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
