<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spreading Word on Health-Care </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Li Fensheng, 46, has spent
five years traveling throughout China to tell people one simple,
but easily neglected fact: There is only one life for a person;
protect your health.
</P>
<P>
Li, who works at Linfen City Procuratorate in north China's
Shanxi Province, said he felt sorry when he saw many people his
age suffering serious diseases or dying because of overwork.
</P>
<P>
That regret caused him to initiate a "health-defending
publicity activity" around the country to arouse people to pay
attention to their own health.
</P>
<P>
Li first gained the support of his wife, a teacher. His wife
spent numerous sleepless nights writing publicity materials.
</P>
<P>
He also visited experts and read medical journals to obtain
health-care knowledge.
</P>
<P>
During a five-year period, he sent out in excess of 4,000
letters, 70 publicity releases and 800 medical books. To do this,
Li spent 25,000 yuan (about 3,120 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Li has traveled through 12 provinces and cities in the
country. Moved by his deeds, dozens of couples have joined his
effort to voluntarily publicize health-care knowledge. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
