<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Primary, Middle School Students Sleep Less, Survey Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 12 (Xinhua) -- A recent survey shows that
nearly 50 percent of local primary school pupils and some 80
percent of middle school students sleep less than nine hours every
night.
</P>
<P>
Too much homework and bad habits are the main reasons behind
their shortened sleeping time, the survey concluded.
</P>
<P>
The survey, involving over 1,000 primary and middle students,
found that students between the fourth grade of primary school and
the third grade of junior middle school all listed "too much
homework" as the No. One factor affecting their sleep.
</P>
<P>
Some homework is given by teachers, some is required by
parents, surveyed students said.
</P>
<P>
Students who do not concentrate while doing their homework,
don't use their spare time constructively, and take up other
unproductive habits are the other most-commonly listed reasons for
shorter sleep time.
</P>
<P>
And too, the fact that some students have to get up early in
the morning to travel a far distance to school can lead to too
little sleep.
</P>
<P>
Concerned experts have called on schools to reduce the amount
of homework to guarantee nine hours of sleep a night for
students. Meanwhile, parents are also asked to help their children
form hood habits and create a favorable environment for their
healthy growth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971112.0193 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Highway for East Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Work has begun on a 142 km
highway from Shangyu to Sanmen, in east China's Zhejiang Province,
according to Tuesday's issue of China Transport News.
</P>
<P>
The project will be built at a total cost of 4.2 billion yuan,
the highest price ever paid for a highway invested by the
province. Construction is scheduled for completion by the year
2000.
</P>
<P>
The road starts in the north at the Shangyu section of the
Hangzhou-Ningbo expressway, and is linked up with Sanmen section
of Ningbo-Wenzhou expressway in the south, passing through five
counties and cities. It is regarded as a "golden passage" between
the coastal and inland areas of Zhejiang. 
</P>
</TEXT>
