<HEADLINE> New Security Company to Open Business in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 12 (Xinhua) -- A poorly-performing
securities company in Fushun, northeast China's Liaoning Province, has
been bought by 15 Shanghai-based companies and will soon be moved
to Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Fushun Securities Co. Ltd. will be renamed "Orient Securities
Co. Ltd.," with its registered capital up from the present 10
million yuan to one billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Orient Securities is the fifth company to locate its
headquarters in Shanghai, the largest trade and financial city of
China, according to officials with the People's Bank of China
Shanghai Branch.
</P>
<P>
The securities company will also take over the 31 security
departments of the Shanghai Pudong Development Bank and the
Shanghai Municipal Cooperative Bank, which will not do business
related to securities and stocks. 
</P>
