<HEADLINE> Health Service to Be Improved in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Uganda is attaching great
importance to public health services in the country, a senior
Ugandan public health official has said.
</P>
<P>
The New Vision today quoted Director General of Health
Services,Kihumuro Apuuli as saying that the 23 billion Uganda
Shillings (some 23 million U.S. dollars) to be received from
Africa Development Bank will be used in rehabilitating health
units throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
The fund is to be used in infrastructure development and in
training health workers, Apuuli told a function on mental illnesses
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Health Ministry has introduced a new health provision
system in the country under which each hospitals in the country
shall provide public health facilities to a particular area, and
district medical officers must do follow-up checks with patients
discharging from hospitals, he said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry was working on the next five-year health policy
which emphasizes provision of health services at the most
cost-effective price, he revealed.
</P>
<P>
Uganda allocated seven U.S. dollars health budget per year for
each one of its some 20 millions population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
