<HEADLINE> Flower Growing Industry Booms in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The flower growing area in
Guangzhou has reached 1,900 hectares, earning it the name "flower
city" of southern China's Guangdong Province, and turning the
industry into an important part of the city's agriculture sector.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou has an annual flower output value of 200 million yuan
(24 million US dollars). The city has more than 400 flower shops
and all of the 130-plus free markets there have flower stalls.
</P>
<P>
The city's Lingnan Flower Wholesale Market has become the
country's biggest flower market, with the highest daily
transaction volume of six million yuan (720,000 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Apart from fresh flowers, potted flowers and potted
landscaping, the city also focuses on the growing of foliage
plants.
</P>
<P>
Guangzhou plans to expand its flower growing area to 2,000
hectares by the end of year 2000, with an annual output value of
400 million yuan (48 million US dollars), and export more than 10
million US dollars-worth of flowers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
