<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa's PPI Inflation Up in September </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, November 12 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's producer
price index (PPI) slightly went up to 6.1 percent in September
from August's 5.9 percent, figures released by the Central
Statistics Service (CSS) Tuesday showed.
</P>
<P>
The increase interrupted the downward trend since the PPI
peaked at 9.6 percent in March.
</P>
<P>
The PPI was pushed up mainly by higher prices for imported
crude oil and agricultural products at home, the CSS said.
</P>
<P>
Economists believe that the PPI rise in September does not
represent a change of the inflation picture. They predicted that
the PPI index will stabilize at 6-6.5 percent next year, compared
with 7.2 percent for this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
