<HEADLINE> Italy Grants Mozambique One Million Dollars in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The Italian government has
provided about one million U.S. dollars to the National Mental
Health Program in Mozambique to help rehabilitate the psychiatric
hospital and other infrastructure in this regard.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed here Tuesday by Giancarlo Santone,
coordinator of Italy's CIES, a non-governmental organization,
according to local newspaper the Noticias today.
</P>
<P>
CIES, which is active in psychiatric field, has already helped
the Infulene Psychiatric Hospital in the suburbs of Maputo in
building a water pump and setting up a document center.
</P>
<P>
The document center has started operation to serve medical
personnel and ordinary people, Santone noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
