<HEADLINE> French Navy Vessel Ends Shanghai Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Vendemiaire, an escort vessel
of the French Navy, left the Chinese Navy's Yangtze port here
today to end a week-long visit.
</P>
<P>
Seeing the vessel off at the port were officials from the
Shanghai Base of the Chinese Navy and Shanghai Government.
</P>
<P>
Officers and men of the two navies had an extensive
communication and contact while the vessel stayed in
Shanghai. Commander Michel Hadengue, captain of the vessel, met
with officials from the Chinese naval force in Shanghai and the
Shanghai city Government respectively, and the crew members
visited China's home designed and manufactured escort vessel as
well as having a look around the city.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai citizens from all walks of life visited the French
vessel. A football match was held between the guests and the
Chinese Navy officers and men. 
</P>
</TEXT>
