<HEADLINE> India Likely to Move WTO Against EU Steel Bar Dumping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government is
considering moving the World Trade Organization (WTO) dispute
settlement mechanism against the European Union's (EU's) recent
initiation of an anti-subsidy case against India's exports of
stainless steel bright bars, official sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The EU had earlier notified the Indian government and the
latter had agreed to hold talks. Yet the EU did not even wait for
the first round of talks but initiated action in the case against
India, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the probe, the EU had initiated an anti-subsidy case
against India's exports of pharmaceutical items, making this the
second case in two months, the sources added.
</P>
<P>
India argues that all the export schemes are "conceptually
designed as reimbursements" and not overt subsidies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
