<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
moved lower at the close today as Asian markets opened weaker.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 17 points lower at 2416 with a turnover
of 66 million NZ dollars (41 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Lion Nathan was the only leader which remained stable. Its
shares ended unchanged at 399 cents.
</P>
<P>
The other major leaders all fell. Telecom dipped 10c to 837c.
Fletcher Energy also slipped 10c to 720c. Brierley Investment
eased 1c to 120c. Carter Holt Harvey shed 5c to 275c and Air New
Zealand dipped 1c to 239c.  
</P>
