<HEADLINE> French President Arrives in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, November 12 (xinhua) -- French President Jacques Chirac
arrived here this morning for a two-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
He was given a red-carpet welcome by Vietnamese President Tran
Duc Luong at the presidential palace.
</P>
<P>
Before starting official talks this afternoon, the two
presidents held a 30-minute private meeting.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's top leader Do Muoi and Prime Minister Phan Van Khai
are scheduled to meet the visiting president respectively.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam and France are expected to sign a number of cooperation
documents this evening including a 350-million-franc (60 million
U.S.dollars ) financial protocol.
</P>
<P>
The visit, two days before the seventh Francophone summit in
Hanoi, aims to enhance Vietnam-France cooperation, particularly in
the economic field, and to help France expand relations with Asian
countries especially those in Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Chirac is the second French president to visit
Vietnam. President Francois Mitterrand visited the country in
February 1993.
</P>
<P>
Chirac is accompanied by foreign minister Hubert Vedrine,
secretary of state for co-operation Charles Josselin, secretary of
state for small and medium-sized enterprises, trade and
handicrafts Marylise Lebranchu and other senior officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
