<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Grand Ecological Project Well Underway in Qinghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, November 12 (Xinhua) -- A grand-scale, trans-century
ecological project in northwest China's plateau province of
Qinghai is well underway and will go far to protect the fragile
local ecological situation.
</P>
<P>
The province accommodates the sources of some major rivers in
China, including the Yangtze, Yellow and Lancang rivers. However,
highland climate and scarce plantation result in severe soil
erosion in an area of 331,400 sq km which makes up 46 percent of
the province's territory.
</P>
<P>
There also exist serious desertification and deteriorating
grasslands. And snowstorms and droughts occur frequently because
of the drastic changes in plateau weather.
</P>
<P>
The ecological project will last till 2030. For the time being,
priority is put on improving forest environment and soil and water
conservation along the upper reaches of the Yellow River.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, ecological agriculture will be boosted and dry
mountains in the province's eastern part will receive
comprehensive treatment. As a result, all farmland will be
terraced by the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
By 2030, more than half of the areas which now suffer from soil
erosion will see improvements.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
