<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0730 GMT, November 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO -- Visiting Chinese Premier Li Peng said here Wednesday
that the nurturing of successors to the older generation in
developing Sino-Japanese friendship now constitutes a major task
for both China and Japan.
</P>
<P>
At a breakfast with five former Japanese prime ministers
Nakasone Yasuhiro, Noburo Takeshita, Toshiki Kaifu, Morihiro
Hosokawa and Tsutomo Hata, Li said China and Japan, both as
countries of major influence in Asia and the world as a whole,
shoulder the task of safeguarding peace and promoting development
at the turn of centuries, and therefore should join efforts in
carrying a long-term stable friendship of good neighborliness
between the two countries into the 21st century.
(Japan-Li Peng-Meeting)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- Four Americans and their Pakistani driver were
killed early Wednesday morning in Pakistan's southern port city of
Karachi, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Americans, who were employees of the Union Texas Company,
were shot dead by unidentified assailants on their way from the
city's Sheraton Hotel to their office, located about three
kilometers away, the sources quoted the Karachi police as
saying. The incident came one day after a 12-member jury declared
a Pakistani national, Aimal Kansi, guilty of killing two CIA
agents and wounding three others in the January, 1993 shooting
outside the Central Intelligence Agency headquarters.
(Pakistan-Americans)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- Romania and the Czech Republic announced Tuesday
that they will resume talks on military cooperation next year,
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made by Romanian Defense Minister Victor
Babiuc and his Czech counterpart, Miloslav Vyborny, at a joint
press conference. Vyborny, who was here for a two-day visit, also
dicussed with Babiuc on bilateral relations and the sitation in
the Balkan region. (Romania-Czech-Military Cooperation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- The Chinese Embassy in Mexico announced that
Chinese President Jiang Zemin will pay a state visit to Mexico
from November 30 to December 3.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice Foreign Minister Li Zhaoxing is in Mexico City to
discuss preparations for Jiang's visit with Mexican Foreign
Minister Miguel Angel Gurria and Vice Foreign Minister Juan
Rebolledo. They agreed to hold a second meeting of political
consultations between Mexico and China, a mechanism created in
1993 for cooperation. (China-Mexico-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PRAGUE -- The Czech Republic will not allow the deployment of
nuclear weapons within its territory, nor allow any bases to be
established there for these weapons, a senior Czech official said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The first deputy foreign minister, Karel Kovanda, said in the
newspaper, "The Rights", that after the Czech Republic's entry
into the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), no foreign
military forces would be deployed in the republic on a permanent
basis. (Czech Republic-NATO)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BELGRADE -- Yugoslav President Slobodan Milosevic said Tuesday
that his coming visit to China aims to further relations between
the two countries and peoples and seek new ways for economic
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Chinese correspondents here, Milosevic
said China's economy has witnessed a relatively high speed of
development in recent years, which will contribute to the whole
world. (Yugoslavia-China) 
</P>
