<HEADLINE> Freedom Forum to Hold Media Forum in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, November 12 (Xinhua) -- An international foundation
of the Freedom Forum is scheduled to conduct its fifth global
media forum in Nairobi on November 13 and 14.
</P>
<P>
Gene Policinski, co-ordinator of special projects at the
Freedom Forum said that two days' discussions and lectures would
include topics such as "media's role in a changing African
society", the Daily Nation reported today.
</P>
<P>
The forum will focus on "News Tradition and Transitions" which
have been discussed in Australia, London, Hong Kong and Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Policinski noted that it was logical to include Africa
because of its importance and the significant development which
has taken place on the continent.
</P>
<P>
According to him, leading journalists and media personalities
from Africa and the U.S. will discuss changes in communications
and technology that have taken place on the continent over the
past decade.
</P>
<P>
They will also explore the growth of on-line information
retrieval services, reporting and media ownership, he added.
</P>
<P>
During the opening dinner tomorrow, Kenyan President Daniel
arap Moi is scheduled to deliver a keynote address entitled
"Kenya's Media: A Presidential View".
</P>
<P>
The final forum in this series will be held in New York next
month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
