<HEADLINE> Four Americans Killed in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Four Americans and their
Pakistani driver were killed early this morning in Pakistan's
southern port city of Karachi, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Americans, who were employees of the Union Texas Company,
were shot dead by unidentified assailants on their way from the
city's Sheraton Hotel to their office, located about three
kilometers away, the sources quoted the Karachi police as saying.
</P>
<P>
The incident came one day after a 12-member jury declared a
Pakistani national, Aimal Kansi, guilty of killing two CIA agents
and wounding three others in the January, 1993 shooting outside
the Central Intelligence Agency headquarters.
</P>
<P>
It also came four days before U.S Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright's Pakistan tour, which is scheduled to start on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the U.S. State Department had advised
Pakistan-based American nationals to observe caution because
"potential threat" existed for retaliation by Kansi sympathizers.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
