<HEADLINE> HK NPC Deputies Election Conference Ends 1st Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The Presidium of the
Conference for Electing Deputies of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) to the Ninth National People's
Congress (NPC) of China made public an announcement upon the close
 of the three-day first session of the Election Conference here
today.
</P>
<P>
The Presidium announced that the Detailed Method for Electing
Deputies of the HKSAR to the Ninth NPC, which was approved at the
plenary session of the Election Conference this morning, is
published for implementation.
</P>
<P>
A Code of Conduct for the 424 members of the Election
Conference, which was also approved at the session, is also
published for implementation, the Announcement said. The purpose
of the Code is to make the election open, just, fair and
successful.
</P>
<P>
Nomination of candidates for HKSAR deputies to the Ninth NPC
will begin Thursday through November 28.
</P>
<P>
Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa, who is also Executive Chairman
of the Presidium of the Election Conference, called on Chinese
citizens among HKSAR residents at age 18 or above to take an
active part in the election.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters at a press briefing after the close of the
first session of the Election Conference, which was held from
November 10 to 12, that the election of NPC deputies in Hong Kong
is very important because the NPC is China's supreme organ of
state power.
</P>
<P>
The 36 NPC deputies to be elected in the HKSAR will represent
Hong Kong to participate in the discussion of major state issues,
which demonstrates that the Hong Kong people not only have the
right to govern Hong Kong, but also have the right to participate
in governing the country, Tung said. 
</P>
