<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Detailed Method for Electing HK NPC Deputies Adopted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The Detailed Method for
Electing Deputies of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(SAR) to the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) of China was
formally adopted at a plenary session of the Election Conference
here today.
</P>
<P>
Three hundred and sixty-eight members of the 424-strong
Election Conference attended today's meeting, and 360 raised their
 hands for the Detailed Election Method, with five against and one
 abstained.
</P>
<P>
The Presidium of the Election Conference formulated a draft of
the Detailed Election Method and presented it to the Election
Conference for discussion Tuesday. Amendments were made to the
draft according to views and opinions expressed by members of the
Election Conference.
</P>
<P>
At today's session, Executive Chairman of the Presidium Tung
Chee Hwa made an explanation of the amendments made to the draft.
</P>
<P>
According to the Detailed Election Method, the number of
deputies to be elected in the HKSAR to the Ninth NPC is 36, and
the NPC deputies to be elected in the HKSAR must be Chinese
citizens among HKSAR residents who are 18 years old or above.
</P>
<P>
Candidates for the NPC deputies must be nominated jointly by at
 least 10 members of the Election conference by filling in the
Nomination Letters.
</P>
<P>
Applicants for the election are asked to fill in Registration
Forms and hand in them together with the Nomination Letters before
 the deadline for nomination at 18:00 hours on November 28.
</P>
<P>
The Presidium of the Election Conference will make public the
list of candidates and distribute it to every member of the
Election Conference.
</P>
<P>
The election is selective with the number of candidates for
deputies to the Ninth NPC exceeding the number to be elected by
from one-fifth to one-half. When the number of nominees exceeds
the number to be elected by more than one-half, there will be a
preliminary round of balloting to narrow the gap.
</P>
<P>
If the number of nominees does not reach the required minimum
of 44 by the deadline, it is up to the Presidium to decide whether
 to extend the deadline for nomination.
</P>
<P>
The Election Conference elects the deputies through secret
balloting, and each member of the Election Conference can select
no more than 36 among the nominees. Candidates are elected on the
merit of votes.
</P>
<P>
The Election Conference will have two chief scrutineers and six
 scrutineers to supervise the distribution, casting and counting
of the ballots.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Election Conference are not allowed to entrust
others to cast ballots on their behalf.
</P>
<P>
The election results will be announced by the Presidium and
reported to the Credentials Commission of the NPC Standing
Committee.
</P>
<P>
The election date is set on December 8. If a preliminary round
of balloting is called for, it will take place on December 6.
</P>
<P>
Today's session also adopted a code of conduct for the members
of the Election Conference for the purpose of making the election
open, just, fair and successful. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971112.0226 </DOCNO>
