<HEADLINE> Uganda Army Reinforces Deployment in Western </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, November 12 (Xinhua) --The Ugandan army deployed 3,000
additional troops in the west to fight the rebel Alled Democratic
Forces (ADF), ''The New Vision'' reported today.
</P>
<P>
Charles Angina, the Operation Commander in the west,has told
local journalists that the troops were deployed in the districts
of kasese, bundibugyo and kabarole where the ADF rebels were
haunting.
</P>
