<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The Independent Commission
Against Corruption (ICAC) of Hong Kong remains firmly committed to
fighting corruption after the handover, ICAC Commissioner Lily Yam
Kwan Pui-ying said today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a regional seminar on corruption-related crime, Yam
pointed out that someone may harbor some doubt about "our
determination and effectiveness" in fighting corruption after July
1.
</P>
