<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Hold Asian Meeting on Mentally Retarded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The 13th Asian International
Conference on Mentally Retarded will be held in Dhaka under the
auspices of the Society for Care and Education of Mentally
Retarded in Bangladesh (SCEMRB), according to the SCEMRB sources
today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 125 delegates from 14 countries and regions as well
as 275 participants representing various government,
non-government and United Nations agencies in Bangladesh will
attend the conference.
</P>
<P>
The conference will add a new chapter in the march towards
establishing the rights and privileges of the mentally retarded in
Bangladesh, according to Prof. M. Shamsul Huq, chairman of the
organizing committee of the conference and former vice-chancellor
of Dhaka University.
</P>
<P>
The theme of the conference is the "Rights of the Mentally
Retarded, Role of the Asian Governments and the United Nations,"
Huq stated.
</P>
<P>
"We seek all-out cooperation from guardians of the retarded
children, social workers, non-government organizations,
politicians and the media people to contribute their best in this
regard," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Asian Federation for the Mentally Retarded, the sources
stated, was first floated in 1973 in Manila in a regional
conference and since then, such conference was held in Japan in
1975, in India in 1977, in Malaysia in 1979, in Hong Kong in 1981,
in Indonesia in 1983, in Taiwan in 1985, in Singapore in 1987, in
Thailand in 1989, in Pakistan in 1991, in South Korea in 1993 and
in Sri Lanka in 1995.  
</P>
</TEXT>
