<HEADLINE> Croatia, Yugoslavia Resume Railway Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Under a Croatia-Yugoslavia
railway transportation agreement, traffic was finally resumed on
all railways between the two countries today since former
Yugoslavia was disintegrated in 1991.
</P>
<P>
The lines stretch from Vinkovci (in Croatia) to Sid (in
Yugoslavia), Vinkovci (in Yugoslavia) to Borovo (in Croatia) and
Erdut (in Croatia) to Subotica (in Yugoslavia).
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed by the two sides here on October 21,
this year.
</P>
<P>
Its implementation shows that they are willing to strengthen
bilateral economic relations, and is also important to their
furthering trade ties with Western and Southern Europe and Middle
East.
</P>
<P>
Croatia and Yugoslavia resumed road traffic in May, last year.
