<HEADLINE> Russia Has Good Harvest This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Russia has gathered in 94
million tons of grain by the end of October, 26.3 percent or 24.7
million tons up from last year, according to the Russian State
Statistical Committee today.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the committee also show that production of
potatos and vegetables reached 33.7 million tons and 8.3 million
tons respectively.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the committee says, the amount of livestock, such as
pigs, cows, chickens, is also on the rise, while milk output per
cow and egg output per hen has increased by more than 5.6 percent
each.
</P>
<P>
The improvement of Russian agriculture is mainly due to the
instituting of various forms of ownership, that give great
incentives to farmers by expanding grain-producing areas.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the Russian government has made available 12 trillion
rubbles (about 2 billion U.S. dollars) in soft loans to ensure an
ample supply of agricultural production materials.
</P>
<P>
Russia is a country with the great potential for agricultural
development. It has the world's largest farming area of 220
million hectares, of which, 134 million are already cultivated.
</P>
</TEXT>
