<DOCNO> XIE19971112.0243 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asbestos Causing Lung Cancer to be Banned from </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, November 12 (Xinhua) -- A type of asbestos used in
tile production can cause lung cancer, a Thai health official said
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Crysotile fibre, a type of asbestos that Thai manufacturers
import to produce tiles, contains a carcinogenic substance that
can cause lung cancer and asbestosis, Wilawan Juengprasert from
the Thai Public Health Ministry was quoted as saying by local
newspapers.
</P>
<P>
The health department of the ministry will seek a ban on the
use of crysotile fibre, she said.
</P>
<P>
Thailand has banned the use of other kinds of asbestos which
contain carcinogenic substances in the production of tile, brake
and clutch pads, and durable cloth, wilawan said.
</P>
<P>
The crysotile fibre currently is the only type still allowed in
the production of these products in Thailand, she said.
</P>
<P>
Crysotile fibre can cause lung cancer, the official said, but
it takes more than 30 years for the symptoms to appear.
</P>
<P>
Thailand currently imports about 100,000 tons of crysotile
fibre each year, she said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
