<HEADLINE> Bangladesh's Foreign Exchange Earnings From Fisheries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh earned 320 million
U.S. dollars from its fishery export during the 1996-97 fiscal
year, the national news agency BSS reported here today.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by State Minister for Fisheries and
Livestock Shatish Chandra Roy while replying a question in the
House Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The state minister told the House that fishery occupied the
third position in last year's export earnings.
</P>
<P>
In the 1996-97 fiscal year, the state minister stated, the
quantity of fishery export was 41,549 tons, earning 14.57 billion
taka (325.22 million dollars), 11.60 billion taka (25 million
dollars) more than the amount of the 1995-96 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh currently produces 1.3 million tons of fish against
an estimated demand of two million tons as projected in the fifth
five-year plan.
</P>
<P>
Last year, shrimp export fetched 13 billion taka (290 million
dollars), which accounted for 89.2 percent of the total earnings
from fishery export, the state minister added.  
</P>
