<HEADLINE> Beijing to Raise Building Quality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Beijing will endeavour to
improve the quality of its project construction, according to
today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zongli, director of the Beijing Construction Commission,
made the remarks yesterday at a working conference on construction
project quality.
</P>
<P>
Next year, Beijing will try to make its key and large projects
reach the world-class level. And the industrial and civil projects
in particular, will all meet quality standards.
</P>
<P>
In the next two years, Wang said, Beijing will Build 50 large
projects including public buildings, infrastructure facilities and
residential zones.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Construction Project Quality Supervision Station
conducted a citywide examination on the completed projects by 117
enterprises, 98 percent have met the standard, up 5 percentage
points from last year's figure.
</P>
<P>
Beijing established a law enforcement brigade in August to
further implement the regulations on the management and quality of
construction projects.
</P>
<P>
In September, the brigade inspected 138 projects under
construction and found quality problems in 45 projects of
them. These were fined a total of 335,000 yuan. 
