<HEADLINE> One More Heroin Refinery Captured in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, November 12 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities
captured one more heroin refinery in Shan State earlier this
month, official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
The refinery, which was found in the Namkhaik area on November
2, was overrun by a combined team of columns of the Northeast
Command of the Myanmar armed forces, local military intelligence
unit and anti-drug squad.
</P>
<P>
The team also seized paraphernalia used in refining heroin and
some other chemicals, the report said.
</P>
<P>
It added that the team also arrested two persons with other
precursor chemicals in another area of Hsenwi on the next day.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, the Myanmar authorities
destroyed 24 heroin refineries in Shan State of the country in the
first four months of this year.  
</P>
