<HEADLINE> Ecuador's Banana Exports Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Ecuador exported 3.69 million
tons of bananas in the first 10 months of 1997, a 17 percent
increase over the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The exports earned 1.09 billion U.S. dollars for the country.
</P>
<P>
In October alone, exports of bananas amounted to 348,289 tons,
7.4 percent above the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
By the end of this year, 4.2 million tons of the fruit will
have been shipped abroad earning more than 1.2 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Banana prices are expected to rise in international markets
because of low production in Central America and the Caribbean
caused by droughts.
</P>
<P>
Ecuador is the biggest banana exporter in the world. Last year
it shipped 3.84 million tons abroad. 
</P>
</TEXT>
