brief Brazil, Mexico, Colombia and Argentina on the nature of the
center.
</P>
<P>
These countries have shown interest in such a project, but
believe that the U.S. military will be involved.
</P>
<P>
Ritter made it clear that the center will have a minimum
participation of the U. S. military.
</P>
<P>
Panama proposed the establishment of the center to be located
in the Howard U.S. Air Base, which will be returned to Panama in
1999 along with the Canal. 
