<HEADLINE> Storm Linda Sinks 185 Thai Trawlers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, November 12 (Xinhua) -- Storm Linda which hit
Thailand's southern and eastern provinces last week sunk 185
trawlers and caused damage to more than 1,000 rai (160 hectares)
of fish and shrimp farms, according to the Fisheries Department of
the Thai government.
</P>
<P>
Search teams found the bodies of seven fishermen, 173 were
rescued and 120 are still missing, Thammarong Prakorbboon,
director-general of the department, was quoted today by local
press as saying.
</P>
<P>
Prachuap Khiri Khan province topped the list of trawler sinking
with 67.
</P>
<P>
Some of the survivors have already been sent home, while rescue
teams from the Fisheries Department, the Navy and the Fish
Marketing Organization have so far recovered 54 fishing boats in
the waters off Prachuap Khiri Khan province.
</P>
<P>
Search and rescue operations were continuing, Thammarong said.
 
</P>
