ministers.
</P>
<P>
They agreed to cooperate in drug supervision, drug prevention
and rehabilitation.
</P>
<P>
A report, to be released soon, showed that one-tenth of the
population in Finland, Norway and Sweden has tried drugs, and the
ratio rose to one third in Denmark.
</P>
<P>
More and more people are becoming victims of powerful
drugs. Drug-related deaths have doubled in Norway and Denmark
since the early 1990s, it said. 
