<HEADLINE> Ukrainian Prices, Currency Stable: Bank Governor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Stable prices and steady currency
are the two noteworthy successes Ukraine has achieved in the
economic sphere, governor of the National Bank of Ukraine (NBU)
said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"The two successes may facilitate the development of a
favorable investment climate in the country," Viktor Yushchenko
said to an international conference "Development and Cooperation
on Banking and Investment Activities" held here.
</P>
<P>
He said the Ukrainian currency, gryvna, which went into
circulation in September 1996, has so far devaluated by only 5
percent.
</P>
<P>
Yushchenko added: "The currency's stability is secured by the
foreign currency reserves of the NBU," that now goes up to 4.7
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
The governor also mentioned that the Ukrainian government has
successfully reined inflation from 39.7 percent in 1996 to about
7.6 percent this year.
</P>
<P>
However, some financial experts disagree with the
governor. "The stability of the gryvna and the low inflation are
achieved at the cost of most Ukrainians' living standards," said a
researcher from the Ukrainian Ministry of Finance.
</P>
<P>
He said prices will skyrocket if every family gets its back
wages and pensions in billions of dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
