<HEADLINE> FIFA Increases Referees for World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, November 11 (Xinhua) -- World soccer ruling body FIFA
is increasing the number of referees for next year's World Cup
finals in France.
</P>
<P>
FIFA's Referees' Committee said in Zurich on Tuesday that it
will appoint 33 referees and 34 assistants for the 64 matches in
France. This compares with 24 referees and 22 assistants for the
52 matches in the United States in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The final names will be announced next February.
</P>
<P>
The committee also approved a special electronic board to
announce substitutions.
</P>
<P>
And it said all referees should be given new uniforms, although
the existing purple-black color will remain unchanged. 
</P>
