<DATE_TIME> 1997-11-11 21:24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 6 Killed in Storms in Kuwait </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, November 11 (Xinhua) -- Six people were killed
today in a torrential rain sweeping Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
A woman was electrocuted and two others drowned in
storm-related accidents, Adel Al-Hashash, an Interior Ministry
official told Kuwaiti television.
</P>
<P>
And three children died when they fell in a water-filled
crater, he said.
</P>
<P>
But so far there was no reports of property damages.
</P>
<P>
About 65 millimeters of rain fell from noon to 6 p.m. local
time.
</P>
<P>
The heavy rain also caused 100 accidents across the country as
many roads were swamped with water and blocked with traffic jams.
</P>
<P>
Airport traffic was reduced in the afternoon and a number of
flights to Kuwait were diverted to airports in neighboring states,
the Kuwaiti News Agency said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
